# ExportFlow - Cursor Rules
# Last Updated: January 30, 2026 - v4 (Renamed + Multi-Tenant)

## =====================================================
## PROJECT OVERVIEW
## =====================================================

**ExportFlow** (anciennement OrderBridge) est une plateforme B2B SaaS multi-tenant pour:
1. Les marques occidentales qui sourcent en Chine
2. Les exportateurs chinois (OEM/ODM) qui vendent Г  l'international

**URLs:**
- Site marketing: `exportflow.io`
- App: `app.exportflow.io`
- Portails clients: `[slug].exportflow.io` (auto-gГ©nГ©rГ©)
- Domaines custom: `orders.clientsite.com` (premium)

**DiffГ©renciateurs clГ©s:**
- Architecture multi-tenant avec sous-domaines automatiques
- Branding personnalisable par client (logo, couleurs, favicon)
- Traduction automatique ENвҶ”CN
- Workflow substitution/rupture avec approbation client
- Suivi paiements T/T (acompte/solde)
- Import Excel super-tolГ©rant (fuzzy SKU matching)
- Interface warehouse chinoise (sans prix)
- Gestion des surcharges modifications tardives

## =====================================================
## ARCHITECTURE MULTI-TENANT
## =====================================================

### Comment Г§a marche

```
1. Client s'inscrit "Swift Boats"
              вҶ“
2. SystГЁme gГ©nГЁre automatiquement:
   вҶ’ slug: "swiftboats"  
   вҶ’ URL: swiftboats.exportflow.io (actif immГ©diatement)
              вҶ“
3. Client personnalise son branding
              вҶ“
4. Option Premium: domaine custom (orders.swiftboats.com)
```

### Configuration DNS (Cloudflare)

```
Type    Name              Content
A       exportflow.io     [IP serveur]
A       app               [IP serveur]
A       *                 [IP serveur]    вҶҗ Wildcard pour tous les tenants
```

### Middleware Next.js

Le middleware intercepte toutes les requГӘtes et:
1. Extrait le sous-domaine du hostname
2. VГ©rifie si c'est un tenant (pas rГ©servГ©)
3. Injecte le `x-tenant-slug` dans les headers
4. L'app charge les donnГ©es du bon tenant

### Sous-domaines rГ©servГ©s

```typescript
const RESERVED = ['app', 'www', 'api', 'admin', 'docs', 'help', 'status', 'blog', 'mail']
```

## =====================================================
## DATA MODELS
## =====================================================

### Company (Tenant)

```typescript
interface Company {
  id: string
  name: string
  slug: string                    // "swiftboats" вҶ’ swiftboats.exportflow.io
  
  // Domaine custom (premium)
  customDomain?: string           // "orders.swiftboats.com"
  customDomainVerified: boolean
  
  // Subscription
  plan: 'starter' | 'growth' | 'pro' | 'enterprise'
  
  // Relations
  branding?: CompanyBranding
  users: User[]
  products: Product[]
  customers: Customer[]
  orders: Order[]
  
  createdAt: Date
  updatedAt: Date
}
```

### CompanyBranding

```typescript
interface CompanyBranding {
  id: string
  companyId: string
  
  // Logos
  logoUrl?: string              // Header logo
  logoSmallUrl?: string         // Favicon / mobile
  logoDarkUrl?: string          // Pour fonds sombres
  invoiceLogoUrl?: string       // Sur les PDFs
  
  // Couleurs
  primaryColor: string          // Default: #0071e3
  primaryHoverColor: string     // Default: #0077ed
  accentColor?: string
  headerBgColor?: string
  headerTextColor?: string
  
  // Contenu
  companyName: string
  tagline?: string
  supportEmail?: string
  supportPhone?: string
  websiteUrl?: string
  
  // Footer
  footerText?: string
  showPoweredBy: boolean        // "Powered by ExportFlow"
  
  // Documents
  invoiceFooter?: string
  
  // AvancГ©
  customCss?: string
}
```

### SubstitutionRequest

```typescript
interface SubstitutionRequest {
  id: string
  orderId: string
  orderLineId: string
  originalProductId: string
  originalQuantity: number
  reason: 'out_of_stock' | 'discontinued' | 'partial_stock' | 'quality_issue'
  
  proposals: SubstitutionProposal[]
  
  status: 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected' | 'expired'
  
  customerResponse?: {
    decision: 'accept' | 'reject' | 'backorder'
    selectedProposalId?: string
    comment?: string
    respondedAt: string
  }
  
  createdAt: string
  expiresAt: string   // Auto-reject aprГЁs 72h
}

interface SubstitutionProposal {
  id: string
  type: 'substitute' | 'backorder'
  productId?: string
  quantity: number
  priceAdjustment: number
  availableDate?: string
  note?: string
}
```

### OrderPayment

```typescript
interface OrderPayment {
  id: string
  orderId: string
  invoiceId?: string
  
  expectedAmount: number
  currency: string
  depositPercentage: number     // Default: 30
  
  payments: PaymentRecord[]
  
  status: 'awaiting_deposit' | 'deposit_received' | 'awaiting_balance' | 'fully_paid' | 'overpaid'
  
  bankDetails: {
    bankName: string
    accountName: string
    accountNumber: string
    swiftCode: string
    reference: string
  }
}

interface PaymentRecord {
  id: string
  type: 'deposit' | 'balance' | 'adjustment'
  amount: number
  currency: string
  receivedDate: string
  paymentMethod: 'tt' | 'lc' | 'paypal' | 'other'
  reference: string
  proofDocument?: string
  verifiedBy?: string
  verifiedAt?: string
  notes?: string
}
```

## =====================================================
## TECH STACK
## =====================================================

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Framework | Next.js 16+ (App Router) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS + CSS Variables |
| State | React Context (TenantContext, DistributorContext) |
| Database | PostgreSQL via Supabase |
| ORM | Prisma 5.x |
| Auth | Custom passwordless OTP |
| PDF | jsPDF |
| DNS/CDN | Cloudflare |
| Hosting | Vercel |
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |

